Name: internal_battery [Resource Attribute]

Name: ci_onboard [Resource Attribute]

Name: shore_networked [Resource Attribute]

Name: geospatial_bounds [Resource Attribute]

Name: ts_updated [Resource Attribute]

Name: width [Resource Attribute]

Name: height [Resource Attribute]

Name: recent_events [Resource Attribute]

Name: stored_data_size [Resource Attribute]

Name: product_download_size_estimated [Resource Attribute]

Text: Gives the power status as a red (alarm condition), yellow (warning,) green (nominal) or black (unassessed/unpowered)

Text: Gives the data status as a red (alarm condition), yellow (warning), green (nominal) or black (unassessed)

Name: location_status_roll_up [Resource Attribute]

Name: hardware_version [Resource Attribute]

Name: last_calibration_datetime [Resource Attribute]

Name: created_by [Resource Attribute]

Name: modified_by [Resource Attribute]

Name: time_zone* [Resource Attribute]
Text: Current time zone set for the user (from the browser setting?)

Name: aggregated_status [Resource Attribute]
Text: Summary of all status indicators, showing red if any individual status indicators are red, yellow if any status individual status indicators are yellow, green if all individual indicators are green or black if unassessed.

Name: reference_urls [Resource Attribute]
Text: URLs with information about the model

Name: required_on_time [Resource Attribute]
Text: Time system must be on before sampling (seconds)

Name: ioos_category [Resource Attribute]
Text: The IOOS  parameter vocabulary term for this data product

Name: exclusive_rights_status [Resource Attribute]
Text: Indicates whether the dataset is under proprietary hold by the PI or whether it is public.  Allowable values: unrestricted, temporary_hold, permanent_hold

Name: exclusive_rights_end_date [Resource Attribute]

Name: exclusive_rights_notes [Resource Attribute]

Name: provenance [Resource Attribute]
Text: Provides an audit trail for the source of the data product (i.e. information on processes, their inputs, the original instrument, etc.)

Name: number_active_subscriptions [Resource Attribute]
Text: The number of current subscriptions to the data

Name: operational_state [Resource Attribute]
Text: The latest known operating condition of a resource, such that a user can easily see whether the resource is commandable, or if not, why not

Name: external_archives [Resource Attribute]
Text: List holding information on where and when the data product was submitted to an external archives, using the ExternalArchive set of fields.

Name: past_user_subscriptions [Resource Attribute]
Text: Provides information for users who have in the past acquired this data product, but for which that acquisition was terminated. The user subscription must be terminated.

Name: deployment_type [Resource Attribute]
Text: PROCESS=One process per resource; SERVICE: One service per resource type

Name: resources [Resource Attribute]
Text: A list of the resources within the collection, via associations

Name: contacts [Resource Attribute]
Text: A list of contact information for entities that serves as a contact points

Name: org_type [Resource Attribute]

Name: label [Resource Attribute]

Name: available_formats [Resource Attribute]

Name: data_ingestion_datetime [Resource Attribute]

Name: data_contents_updated [Resource Attribute]

Text: a link to the (time-varying) data product. Mandatory

Name: attachment_type [Resource Attribute]

Name: GeospatialCoordinateReferenceSystem [Object Type]
Text: Hold information about the geospatial coordinate reference system(s) used

Name: TemporalBounds [Object Type]
Text: Defines a time bounds through a start and end datetime pair

Name: street_address [Object Field]
Text: the street address portion of the mailing address

Name: phones [Object Field]
Text: Lists the stored attributes of Phone objects

Name: individual_names_given [Object Field]
Text: the given, i.e. first and optionally middle, name(s)

Name: organization_name [Object Field]
Text: name of the organization.  Can be used in place of an individually-named contact when appropriate

Name: country [Object Field]
Text: the country part of the address

Name: administrative_area [Object Field]
Text: Any place names that are less specific than country and more specific than city, e.g. state or province.

Name: description [Object Field]
Text: readable description of the event (not required)

Name: origin [Object Field]
Text: the origin of the event (content specific to subtype). Mostly a resource id

Name: origin_type [Object Field]
Text: the type of origin (e.g. resource type, etc.) or empty

Name: sub_type [Object Field]
Text: A specialization of the event_type expressed by this object type (or empty)

Name: ts_created [Object Field]
Text: Timestamp of event created in milliseconds in UNIX epoch

Name: geospatial_geodetic_crs [Object Field]
Text: The geospatial  coordinate reference system, expressed as a URI (ideally a URL); incorporates both coordinate system and datum; may be geodetic horizontal, vertical, or both

Name: geospatial_vertical_crs [Object Field]
Text: the vertical coordinate reference system, expressed as a URI (ideally a URL); incorporates both coordinate system and datum

Name: geospatial_latitude_units [Object Field]
Text: specifies the units of measure for latitude

Name: geospatial_longitude_units [Object Field]
Text: specifies the units of measure for longitude

Name: geospatial_vertical_units [Object Field]
Text: specifies the units of measure for the vertical location; overrides the geospatial_vertical_crs, if those units are different

Name: geospatial_vertical_positive [Object Field]
Text: specifies the direction meant by more positive vertical location values; up indicates more positive values are further from earth's center

Name: geospatial_vertical_location [Object Field]
Text: specifies a vertical position (relative to the datum, along the axis direction specified by geospatial_vertical_positive)

Name: geospatial_vertical_accuracy [Object Field]
Text: the accuracy of the vertical value, expressed in the same units

Name: connection_port [Object Field]
Text: unique identification of the port to which the deployed device is attached (let's say a CV term appropriate to the parent device)

Name: offset_x [Object Field]
Text: offset location of the mounted device along the Y axis of the mounting platform, with more positive offsets indicating the device is further along the positive direction of that axis and  indicating the device is at the origin of the axis (see https://confluence.oceanobservatories.org/display/CIDev/Coordinate+Systems+and+Coordinate+Transformations#CoordinateSystemsandCoordinateTransformations-MountingPosition)

Name: offset_y [Object Field]
Text: offset location of the mounted device along the Z axis of the mounting platform, with more positive offsets indicating the device is further along the positive direction of that axis and  indicating the device is at the origin of the axis (see https://confluence.oceanobservatories.org/display/CIDev/Coordinate+Systems+and+Coordinate+Transformations#CoordinateSystemsandCoordinateTransformations-MountingPosition)

Name: offset_z [Object Field]
Text: offset location of the mounted device along the X axis of the mounting platform, with more positive offsets indicating the device is further along the positive direction of that axis andd  indicating the device is at the origin of the axis (seehttps://confluence.oceanobservatories.org/display/CIDev/Coordinate+Systems+and+Coordinate+Transformations#CoordinateSystemsandCoordinateTransformations-MountingPosition)

Name: rotation_x [Object Field]
Text: indicates which way a device is pointing relative to its platform; specifies the rotation around the X axis (the first rotation offset) in degrees clockwise; assumes device is pointing out Z axis (see https://confluence.oceanobservatories.org/display/CIDev/Coordinate+Systems+and+Coordinate+Transformations#CoordinateSystemsandCoordinateTransformations-MountingOrientation)

Name: rotation_y [Object Field]
Text: indicates which way a device is pointing relative to its platform; specifies the rotation around the Y axis (the second rotation offset, after the X rotation) in degrees clockwise; assumes device is pointing out Z axis (see https://confluence.oceanobservatories.org/display/CIDev/Coordinate+Systems+and+Coordinate+Transformations#CoordinateSystemsandCoordinateTransformations-MountingOrientation)

Name: rotation_z [Object Field]
Text: indicates which way a device is pointing relative to its platform; specifies the rotation around the Z axis (the last rotation offset, after the X and Y rotations) in degrees clockwise; assumes device is pointing out Z axis (see https://confluence.oceanobservatories.org/display/CIDev/Coordinate+Systems+and+Coordinate+Transformations#CoordinateSystemsandCoordinateTransformations-MountingOrientation)

Name: phone_number [Object Field]
Text: The phone number.  phone number is assumed US if no '+' prefix exists to specify a country code

Name: ooi_short_name [Object Field]
Text: The 7 character code (now being expanded to >7 characters) used by COL to identify core data products, e.g. TEMPWAT)

Name: fill_value [Object Field]
Text: indicates the value that codes for a missing value

Name: axis [Object Field]
Text: For CF compliance, holds X, Y, Z or T for variables holding lat, lon, depth, and time info, respectively

Name: description [Object Field]
Text: a human-readable description of the parameter

Name: characteristic_name [Object Field]
Text: Name of the characteristic being reported on. Common ones include accuracy, precision, and drift

Name: units [Object Field]
Text: The units associated with the value of the characteristic

Name: applicable_range_min [Object Field]
Text: If the value is only valid within a particular range, this gives the minimum. Must be in same units as the value.

Name: applicable_range_max [Object Field]
Text: If the value is only valid within a particular range, this gives the maximum. Must be in same units as the value.

Name: source [Object Field]
Text: Indicates the category of the source of the value, such as manufacturer, literature, etc.

Name: start_datetime [Object Field]
Text: The start of the time span

Name: end_datetime [Object Field]
Text: The end of the time span
